Research Title: Acoustically Conditioned Gated Fusion Matrices for Cross-Modal Empathy and Low-Latency Emergency Interception in Clinical Voice Agents

The Scientific Gap: Conventional modular and semi-multimodal edge health assistants suffer from "Acoustic Blindness". They treat patient audio transcripts as purely textual representations. If an acute cardiovascular patient gasps "My chest feels tight" due to an active myocardial infarction, a standard ASR-to-LLM pipeline strips away the vital acoustic markers of physical trauma (e.g., altered fundamental frequency F 
0

 , high jitter, breathless pauses). The text engine receives the exact same character array as a calm patient reading a baseline report, resulting in detached, templated empathy responses and delayed medical escalations. Furthermore, routing complex diagnostic choices entirely through an LLM introduces a processing bottleneck, which is unsafe during real-world respiratory emergencies.  
